Commentary Text: Tymal Mills to Dhawan, 1 run, Tymal Mills appeals for an LBW thinking it is pad-first. Huge inside-edge on that and Dhawan will take a single to the backward point region. Tails back in, at middle and leg, Dhawan gets an edge onto pad on the push. Guess what MI have reviewed this and will lose it. The side-on angle shows the ball to be flicking the front pad first, Tymal Mills and Rohit are wondering why it wasn't given as they see it on the big screen. The onfield umpire chats to Rohit and I think explains the logic behind the call. More replays are in: The ball flicked the front pad's strap before the inside-edge

Commentary Text: Vaibhav Arora to Pollard, out Pollard Run Out!! 1 run completed. Suicidal running! 140.9kph, very full delivery outside off, Pollard bunts it down to long-on. There's a slight misfield from Smith who slips after running to his right and SKY signals his partner to come back for the second while Pollard put his hand up and said NO. An accurate throw at the keeper's end and Jitesh Sharma breaks the stumps to catch Pollard short of his ground. Suryakumar Yadav turns back and watches it angrily. Clearly, the second run wasn't on. SKY initially wanted the second, but he stopped. It was Pollard who then had to sacrifice his wicket as Surya crossed over. Pollard run out (Odean Smith/Jitesh Sharma) 10(11) [4s-1]
